01/11/2010
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Police announced on Sunday (October 31st) they have seized parts of a bronze burial chariot dating from the 2nd century AD. 
The objects were discovered during raids in the homes of two people, during an operation to recover stolen antiquities. 
Authorities believe that the other parts of the chariot have already been sold abroad. 
During the searches, police also found also objects from the Roman period and two icons. 
(Sitel, Inpres, AP - 31/10/10)
